translated: Lundeli, Torsten Valdemar, estate owner, captain. Born on May 19, 1889 in Uppsala to Professor Johan August L. and Marie-Louise Jönsson. Married on the 24th of the month with Aina Lundberg. - Studied in Uppsala; completed high school in 1907 and earned a bachelor's degree in 1916. Second lieutenant in the Uppland Regiment from 1914, promoted to lieutenant in 1917, and captain in 1938. Served in Russia, Japan, USA, and several European countries. Amsterdam as part of the Swedish legation in Petrograd from 1917-1918, awarded the Swedish Red Cross for service in Russia and Siberia from 1918-1919, secretary of the Swedish relief committee for prisoners of war in Siberia and leader of aid expeditions from 1920-1921. Owner of Ebbe-torps estate from 1923. Member of the second chamber of the Swedish Parliament from 1933-1944, county councilman from 1942-1946. Vice chairman of the board for the Southern Kalmarsund Dairy Federation from 1932, board member of the Southern Kalmarsund Grain Growers' Association from 1934, board chairman of the Kalmar County Dairy Federation from 1939, board member of the Kalmar Canning Factory Ltd. from 1930, and more. Awarded the Royal Order of Vasa in 1941.
